  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project Concern International (PCI)&#xD5;s OVC and Gender Project will improve the quality of life of orphans and vulnerable children, and their parents/caregivers through enhancing gender-based responses and programming in HIV/AIDS activities in Botswana over a five year period. PCI Botswana will achieve this in close partnership with implementing organizations Catholic Relief Services (CRS), Hope World Wide Botswana (HWWB), Humana People to People (HPP), Marang Child Care Network Trust (MCCNT); the Government of Botswana (GOB); and a diverse array of community and private sector organizations.</narrative>
